# Read CLAUDE.md first (non-negotiable)

Applies to **Cursor Agent**, **Composer**, and **subagents** in this repository.

## Required first action

1. **First tool call** in the conversation (and at the start of each new subagent) MUST be `Read` on `CLAUDE.md` at the repository root.
2. Do this **before** any other tool: skills, search, terminal, edits, MCP, or a substantive reply.
3. **`@CLAUDE.md` in rules does not replace this** — you must still run `Read` so the full current file is loaded.
4. After `Read`, obey every section in `CLAUDE.md` for the rest of the task (including `memory.md` / Graphify per §5–§6).

## When to skip

Never skip for “simple” questions, greetings, or “just a quick look”. Only skip if you **already** called `Read` on `CLAUDE.md` earlier in **this** conversation and you have not started a new subagent.

## On failure

If `Read` fails (missing path, permission), say so and stop until the path is fixed — do not guess defaults.

@CLAUDE.md
